abstract: A lawsuit by 10 state attorneys general to block the $26 billion takeover could kill the transaction — or at least tie it up in the courts for ages.

abstract: Josh Tyrangiel is out after a four-year run. Jesse Angelo, the former publisher of The New York Post, is set to come aboard.
snippet: Josh Tyrangiel is out after a four-year run. Jesse Angelo, the former publisher of The New York Post, is set to come aboard.
lead_paragraph: There were significant changes at Vice Media on Monday as the company — which was once operated more like a frat party than a business — takes shape under new leadership.

headline_main: DealBook Briefing: Meet the New Defense Industry Giant

abstract: She spent her teenage years in Lower Manhattan before raising a family in Puerto Rico. Now she’s back for good.
snippet: She spent her teenage years in Lower Manhattan before raising a family in Puerto Rico. Now she’s back for good.
lead_paragraph: In 1966, when she was 11, Ruth Santiago moved from Puerto Rico to an apartment on Pitt Street, on the Lower East Side, with her parents and five brothers. The youngest of 17 children, Ms. Santiago had many older siblings already living in New York by then, which made the move feel like an adventure and a homecoming.

abstract: Chronic insomnia is linked to an increased risk of developing hypertension, Type 2 diabetes, heart attack, depression, anxiety and premature death.

lead_paragraph: How did you sleep last night? If you’re over 65, I hope it was better than many others your age. In a study by the National Institute on Aging of over 9,000 Americans aged 65 and older, more than half said they had difficulty falling asleep or staying asleep. Many others who believe they spend an adequate number of hours asleep nonetheless complain of not feeling rested when they get up.

abstract: The Treasury secretary also said that President Trump will meet with China’s leader, Xi Jinping, at the G-20 leaders’ summit in Osaka, Japan, later this month.
snippet: The Treasury secretary also said that President Trump will meet with China’s leader, Xi Jinping, at the G-20 leaders’ summit in Osaka, Japan, later this month.
lead_paragraph: FUKUOKA, Japan — The icy relationship between the United States and China over trade showed no signs of easing on Saturday, as Treasury Secretary Steven Mnuchin called on Beijing to return to talks and follow through on its commitments or face more tariffs from President Trump.
